<zk>
	<label multiline="true">
		To test this case, the bundled B104-ZK-6101-zk.xml configures automatic-timeout with
		timer-keep-alive=false and a short session-timeout. After ~12s the desktop expires;
		the ignorable onTimer AU request must still trigger the redirect to /timeout.zul.

		Expected: the page is redirected to "/timeout.zul" within ~15s, even though only the
		ignorable onTimer request observes the timeout.
	</label>
	<zscript><![CDATA[
	void tick() {
		// No-op; just keep the timer firing ignorable onTimer requests.
	}
	]]></zscript>
	<timer id="timer" delay="1000" repeats="true" onTimer="tick()" onCreate="self.start()"/>
</zk>
